I just rolled the
same die, just like I

00:31:47.824 --> 00:31:49.950
did in that demonstration,
and then I got a 9.

00:31:49.950 --> 00:31:54.110
OK, so now we have a sequence
of two pieces of data, 5 and 9.

00:31:54.110 --> 00:32:06.120
So I want to find the posterior
that-- update in two steps.

00:32:06.120 --> 00:32:07.590
I'm doing this one.

