00:32:35.070 --> 00:32:36.050
possibilities.

00:32:36.050 --> 00:32:37.300
We multiply.

00:32:37.300 --> 00:32:39.090
That gives us our
unnormalized posterior

00:32:39.090 --> 00:32:40.630
for the first piece of data.

00:32:40.630 --> 00:32:41.420
Great.

00:32:41.420 --> 00:32:45.620
Now that is going
to be our new prior.

00:32:45.620 --> 00:32:47.570
Now, you may complain,
