00:33:03.700 --> 00:33:04.200
OK?

00:33:04.200 --> 00:33:06.020
So it saves you
work to not bother

00:33:06.020 --> 00:33:08.951
to normalize the first time.

00:33:08.951 --> 00:33:09.450
Great.

00:33:09.450 --> 00:33:11.440
So that's our new prior.

00:33:11.440 --> 00:33:13.740
We get our next
piece of data, the 9.

00:33:13.740 --> 00:33:18.460
We have 0, 0, 0, 1/12, and
